content.description:
The nicest route on this little buttress, some nice moves. 

  The crux, as usual for Devils Lake, is at the bottom above a rocky landing.  Definitely height dependent - easier if you are tall.
content.location: As you head North along the base, this is on the NE side of the first buttress.

content.description: A fun little face climb.  The difficulty depends on how strict you are about staying off holds in the chimney to the left ...
content.location: On the face between "Your Name in Lights" and the "Star-maker Chimney."

content.description:
Will you be a star, or will you be seeing stars? 

  Requires almost no chimney technique:  look for little ledges and sidepulls inside the chimney, and feet on the face outside.
content.protection: A couple of 4" pieces will tame the runout.  Standard stuff above.
content.location: On the first buttress (counting from the South), the obvious chimney on the left side.

content.description:
Listed as #9 in Sven's guidebook this is a hidden gem. 

  Climb the rib on the left side and through the notch in the overhang.
content.location: Rightside of Hollywood and Vines. Look for the off-color rib to a notched roof.

content.description:
The name refers to Remo's ability to climb this flawlessly and then absolutely FAIL trying to climb the next door "Never Again" with the same rating. 

  Three variations exist, with the right face topping out as 5.10b. These routes are listed in Sven's guide as #5 and #6. 

  Variation 1: Start on the right side of the nose and 1/3 of the way traverse left and finish on the crack above. 

  Variation 2: Same start but avoid the crack on the left at the top, 5.10a. 

  Variation 3: Same start but go straight up right of the nose, 5.10b.
content.location: Right of "Never Again" is a corner with a smooth face above.

content.description: Off-fist crack to finish an easy scramble.
#8 in the Climber's Guide. Climb wall with three large flakes.
content.protection: Medium nuts mostly, a small cam or two

content.description: Crux is the first 10 feet.  Getting feet established up onto large triangular sloping divot/ledge along crack.
content.protection: Good pro all the way up with gear from mid-sized fingers up to medium fist size.
content.location: Climb the crack line just left of the route Flake Fun.  Climb starts as a steep straight in crack that turns quickly into a right facing corner then up into a tricky downward facing flake just below upper finishing block.   Lost of dirt/leaves/ferns etc.  Crux is the first 10 feet and has great protection.

content.description:
Although this is just off the trail, it remains an obscure (and nicely shady) area.

 The bouldering here is known as 1.  The Instrumentals

.

 Be sure to check out the lower level ("The Bottom") while you are here.
